@startuml
!include theme.iuml
title End-to-End Booking — Admission, Atomic Lock, Saga and Compensation
autonumber
actor Customer
participant "Web Client" as Web
participant "API Gateway" as API
participant "Waiting Room" as Waiting
participant "Reservation Engine" as Reservation
collections "Redis" as Redis
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Billing Orchestrator" as Billing
participant "External Gateway" as Gateway
queue "RabbitMQ" as MQ
participant "Notification Worker" as Worker
Customer -> Web: Open high-demand event
Web -> API: POST /waiting-room/{event}/join (JWT)
API -> Waiting: enqueue(event, user)
Waiting -> Redis: INCR event sequence
Waiting -> DB: persist QUEUED / ADMITTED entry
Waiting --> Web: position or admissionToken + expiry
loop Until admitted (bounded polling / WebSocket)
  Web -> API: GET /waiting-room/{entry}
  API --> Web: state + position
end
Web -> API: POST /reservations\n(event, seats, admissionToken)
API -> Waiting: validate token, user, event, TTL
API -> Reservation: reserve seats
Reservation -> DB: validate published event, venue and pricing
Reservation -> Redis: EVAL atomic multi-key acquire\n(all absent => PSETEX all, 10 min)
alt any key already exists
  Redis --> Reservation: conflict (no partial locks)
  Reservation --> Web: 409 seat unavailable
else all keys acquired
  Redis --> Reservation: acquired
  Reservation -> DB: BEGIN; recheck UNIQUE(eventId, seatId)\ninsert PENDING reservation + price snapshots; COMMIT
  Reservation --> Web: reservation + expiresAt + total
end
Web -> API: POST /payments\n(reservationId, idempotencyKey)
API -> Billing: create or return existing payment
Billing -> Gateway: authorize/capture(reference, amount)
alt definitive success before reservation expiry
  Gateway --> Billing: success + providerReference
  Billing -> DB: BEGIN (pessimistic payment lock)\nCONFIRMED + BOOKED + immutable tickets; COMMIT
  Billing -> Redis: owner-checked release
  Billing -> MQ: payment.succeeded + ticket.issued
  Billing --> Web: ticket metadata
else decline
  Gateway --> Billing: declined
  Billing -> DB: BEGIN; FAILED + CANCELLED\ndelete transient inventory; COMMIT
  Billing -> Redis: owner-checked release
  Billing -> MQ: payment.failed
  Billing --> Web: compensated failure
else timeout / uncertain response
  Gateway x-- Billing: timeout
  Billing -> Gateway: bounded status reconciliation
  alt payment is unknown or failed at TTL
    Billing -> DB: TIMEOUT + EXPIRED + compensation
    Billing -> Redis: owner-checked release
    Billing -> MQ: payment.failed
  else gateway confirms success
    Billing -> DB: idempotent success transition
  end
end
MQ -> Worker: durable delivery
Worker -> DB: persist notification outcome
Worker --> Customer: Email / SMS
@enduml
